{"word":"H8040 - שְׂמֹאול - sᵉmôʼwl - sem-ole' - Left","slug":"H8040","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">שְׂמֹאול</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>sᵉmôʼwl"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>sem-ole'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Left"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E9;&#x05C2;&#x05DE;&#x05D0;&#x05DC;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#x05E9;&#x05C2;&#x05DE;&#x05D0;&#x05D5;&#x05DC; - s&#x0301;<sup>e</sup>mo&#x0302;'l  s&#x0301;<sup>e</sup>m'o&#x0302;l</b> - <i>sem-ole', sem-ole'</i><p/>A primitive word (rather perhaps from the same as <a href=\"#/H8071\">H8071</a> (by insertion of the <i>'aleph</i>) through the idea of <i>wrapping</i> up); properly <i>dark</i> (as <i>enveloped</i>), that is, the <i>north</i>; hence (by orientation) the <i>left</i> hand: - left (hand, side)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H8041\">H8041</a>, <a href=\"#/H8042\">H8042</a>"}]}